Description: CDE (Common Desktop Environment) theme for KDE Plasma 5
 A complete recreation of the early-90s Common Desktop Environment look
 for KDE Plasma 5, including:
   - KWin window decoration with CDE-style beveled borders and L-shaped
     resize corners
   - Qt5 widget style (buttons, scrollbars, flat progress bars)
   - Plasma desktop theme (panel, system tray, plasmoids)
   - SDDM login theme
   - Lock screen overlay
   - Multiple bundled color schemes (Blue-Gray, Dark, Chartreuse, Electric Pink)
 .
 This is the Plasma 5 build. For Plasma 6, use the main cde-plasma package
 from a release targeting Debian 13 / Ubuntu 24.10 or later.
 .
 After installation, run `cde-plasma-apply` as your user to switch to the
 theme. Run `cde-plasma-unapply` to revert (the package stays installed).
